00:38:40,901 --> 00:38:41,985
Drifters.

526
00:38:42,111 --> 00:38:44,404
Delaney said I should stop by.

527
00:38:44,530 --> 00:38:46,364
Don't mean nothing to me.

528
00:38:46,490 --> 00:38:48,199
lf you want to get this thing
up on time,

529
00:38:48,326 --> 00:38:49,492
you're gonna need another man.

530
00:38:49,618 --> 00:38:51,536
I don't need your
calculations, college-boy.

531
00:38:51,662 --> 00:38:52,871
Love you too, Byrnes.

532
00:38:52,997 --> 00:38:55,915
Sir, l'm sorry to bother you,
but, uh...

533
00:38:56,042 --> 00:38:56,958
l need the work.

534
00:38:57,084 --> 00:38:58,835
l got a boy I need to feed.

535
00:39:02,882 --> 00:39:03,923
You a thief?

536
00:39:04,050 --> 00:39:05,216
No, sir,
l'm a God-fearing man.

537
00:39:05,343 --> 00:39:07,344
Christian, huh?

538
00:39:09,722 --> 00:39:11,222
Well, what can you do,
Christian?

539
00:39:11,349 --> 00:39:12,724
You name it,
anything, sir.

540
00:39:12,850 --> 00:39:14,100
Cement mixing and stonework?

541
00:39:14,226 --> 00:39:16,269
Sir, masonry, metalwork.

542
00:39:16,395 --> 00:39:18,104
Got a real talent with wood.

543
00:39:18,230 --> 00:39:19,105
When can you start?

544
00:39:19,231 --> 00:39:21,816
Right now, sir.

545
00:39:21,942 --> 00:39:23,276
You go see the big Swede
over there.

546
00:39:23,402 --> 00:39:24,611
Swede?

547
00:39:24,737 --> 00:39:26,029
- That's right.
- Thank you, sir.

548
00:39:28,657 --> 00:39:30,075
Sorry to bother you.

549
00:39:30,201 --> 00:39:31,826
All right, let's move it!

550
00:39:31,952 --> 00:39:33,119
Matthew Wakefield.

551
00:39:33,245 --> 00:39:34,245
Call me Swede.

552
00:39:41,796 --> 00:39:43,046
Come on, Mark.

553
00:39:48,427 --> 00:39:50,720
<i>"Dear Mark and Luke,</i>

554
00:39:50,846 --> 00:39:55,308
<i>"l hope you boys are behaving
for Aunt Coral and Uncle Jonas.</i>

555
00:39:55,434 --> 00:39:58,228
<i>"l know you don't understand
why I had to go,</i>

556
00:39:58,354 --> 00:40:01,856
<i>"but I'll be back soon.</i>

557
00:40:01,982 --> 00:40:04,567
<i>"l found a job in a place
where we can start over,</i>

558
00:40:04,693 --> 00:40:06,903
<i>"be a family again.</i>

559
00:40:07,029 --> 00:40:10,990
<i>"John and I miss you two
so much.</i>

560
00:40:11,117 --> 00:40:13,451
<i>Your loving father."</i>

561
00:40:14,912 --> 00:40:16,913
Swede, I know you don't like
to hear this, but...

562
00:40:17,039 --> 00:40:18,331
the Russians
were on to something.

563
00:40:18,457 --> 00:40:20,375
Mark my words, in our lifetime,

564
00:40:20,501 --> 00:40:22,127
we will see men
living on the moon.

565
00:40:22,253 --> 00:40:24,379
lf it'll make these things
lighter, l'm all for it.

566
00:40:24,505 --> 00:40:25,547
Whoa-ho!

567
00:40:25,673 --> 00:40:27,006
Swede, you hear that?

568
00:40:27,133 --> 00:40:30,301
We just got our first complaint
from the man after one month.

569
00:40:30,428 --> 00:40:31,678
Swede, you owe me a buck.

570
00:40:31,804 --> 00:40:33,847
Only if you tell me why
they are lighter.

571
00:40:33,973 --> 00:40:35,014
That's easy.

572
00:40:35,141 --> 00:40:36,516
They'd be lighter
because on the moon,

573
00:40:36,642 --> 00:40:38,017
there's a weaker force
of gravity.

574
00:40:38,144 --> 00:40:39,018
Bullshit.

575
00:40:39,145 --> 00:40:40,186
You're so full of it, Diploma.

576
00:40:40,312 --> 00:40:42,105
No, gentlemen, I read.

577
00:40:42,231 --> 00:40:44,107
And with knowledge comes power.

578
00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:45,191
Swede.

579
00:40:45,317 --> 00:40:48,278
Give the ltalian a hand.

580
00:40:49,947 --> 00:40:51,364
Now, you two knock off early.

581
00:40:51,490 --> 00:40:52,532
And be on time tomorrow.

582
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:54,701
We're pouring the cement.

583
00:40:54,827 --> 00:40:56,369
Christian.

584
00:40:56,495 --> 00:40:58,246
l need to talk to you.

585
00:41:00,833 --> 00:41:03,918
All right, l'm gonna go get
drunk, you coming?

586
00:41:04,044 --> 00:41:05,503
Yeah, fine.

587
00:41:09,842 --> 00:41:11,801
We can't have this anymore.

588
00:41:11,927 --> 00:41:13,136
He ain't done no harm
to nobody.

589
00:41:13,262 --> 00:41:14,137
l told you when I signed on,

590
00:41:14,263 --> 00:41:15,346
l ain't got no place for him.

591
00:41:15,473 --> 00:41:19,726
Look, Christian,
l come to like your kid.

592
00:41:19,852 --> 00:41:21,060
l'd even ask some folks,

593
00:41:21,187 --> 00:41:24,147
but I don't think
they could handle his quirks.

594
00:41:24,273 --> 00:41:26,024
l'm a good worker, ain't l?

595
00:41:26,150 --> 00:41:28,276
You're the best worker I got.

596
00:41:28,402 --> 00:41:29,944
But you getting fired
and me getting fired

597
00:41:30,070 --> 00:41:31,154
is two different things.

598
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:32,739
Now, you can come to work
tomorrow or not,

599
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:34,532
but you can't bring the kid.

600
00:41:41,790 --> 00:41:44,501
- Come on.
- Okay.

601
00:41:44,627 --> 00:41:46,544
Spin me, Pa.

602
00:41:46,670 --> 00:41:48,463
Whee!

603
00:42:07,566 --> 00:42:11,653
Fiola and Kramer
Toys and Novelties.

604
00:42:11,779 --> 00:42:13,821
Went out of business
in the early '70s.

605
00:42:13,948 --> 00:42:17,534
And I looked into this.

606
00:42:17,660 --> 00:42:18,952
Yeah?
What'd you find out?

607
00:42:19,078 --> 00:42:21,204
My best guess is that
it's some sort of toy.

608
00:42:24,750 --> 00:42:25,959
Good job.

609
00:42:26,085 --> 00:42:29,837
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

610
00:43:26,979 --> 00:43:28,479
<i>You've reached the office
of the warden</i>

611
00:43:28,606 --> 00:43:29,939
<i>at Pleasant Valley
state prison.</i>

612
00:44:05,184 --> 00:44:08,895
Yeah, Lisa.

613
00:44:09,021 --> 00:44:11,064
lt's Tom.

614
00:44:11,190 --> 00:44:13,149
l want you to look into
something for me.

615
00:44:14,985 --> 00:44:16,110
I just love all the work

616
00:44:16,236 --> 00:44:18,071
you've put into remodeling
the house,

617
00:44:18,197 --> 00:44:21,240
but I can't find a single thing.

618
00:44:24,703 --> 00:44:27,872
Thought it would be nice
to mix it up.

619
00:44:27,998 --> 00:44:30,583
Barbara?

620
00:44:30,709 --> 00:44:32,251
Hmm?

621
00:44:43,055 --> 00:44:44,222
lt's okay.

622
00:44:44,348 --> 00:44:46,641
l'll get something to clean it.

623
00:44:55,484 --> 00:44:58,069
You know, Barbara, we've got
plenty of the plain.

624
00:44:58,195 --> 00:45:00,488
l just thought it'd be nice
to mix it up.

625
00:45:02,950 --> 00:45:09,288
Barbara?

626
00:45:49,496 --> 00:45:51,831
He doesn't like anyone
to come in here.

627
00:45:54,960 --> 00:45:57,962
l can't live like this anymore.

628
00:45:58,088 --> 00:46:02,258
- No, you can't.
- Hello?

629
00:46:02,384 --> 00:46:04,051
Barb?

630
00:46:04,178 --> 00:46:07,805
We'll be right there, Tom.

631
00:46:21,653 --> 00:46:23,780
- How was your day?
- Pretty good.

632
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:27,658
So Barb will be down
in a minute.

633
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:29,660
Sit down;
l'll make you a cup of coffee.

634
00:46:29,787 --> 00:46:31,579
You can tell me all about
that boy you found.

635
00:47:15,749 --> 00:47:18,709
I want to have Tommy, Jr.
declared legally dead.

636
00:47:23,966 --> 00:47:26,050
lt's time, Tom.

637
00:47:29,680 --> 00:47:32,682
l can't keep pretending
that he is gonna come home.

638
00:47:35,394 --> 00:47:36,853
l'm not talking about this
right now.

639
00:47:36,979 --> 00:47:39,021
And l'm not letting it go
this time.

640
00:47:39,147 --> 00:47:40,857
We have to come
to an understanding.

641
00:47:40,983 --> 00:47:42,984
l can't live like this anymore.

642
00:47:47,155 --> 00:47:48,364
l want to clean out his room.

643
00:47:48,490 --> 00:47:50,366
Barb, you have no idea
what you're talking about.

644
00:47:50,492 --> 00:47:53,286
He wouldn't even be
that 10-year-old boy anymore.

645
00:47:53,412 --> 00:47:55,204
You don't touch anything
until there is a body.

646
00:47:55,330 --> 00:47:57,582
He would be 18,
already a man.

647
00:47:57,708 --> 00:47:58,791
l'm warning you.

648
00:47:58,917 --> 00:47:59,792
Just say it.

649
00:47:59,918 --> 00:48:02,920
Just say it, Tom.

650
00:48:03,046 --> 00:48:06,007
Just say,
"My son is dead."

651
00:48:33,285 --> 00:48:34,869
- Thanks, Dan.
- lt's okay.

652
00:48:34,995 --> 00:48:36,329
Look, I know
what you're gonna say,

653
00:48:36,455 --> 00:48:37,413
but just hear me out.

654
00:48:37,539 --> 00:48:38,664
You know you can't
talk to him.

655
00:48:38,790 --> 00:48:39,999
lt's not about that.

656
00:48:40,125 --> 00:48:42,126
l want to talk to him
about this kid we just found.

657
00:48:42,252 --> 00:48:43,794
Yeah, sure.

658
00:48:43,921 --> 00:48:45,838
You have been up my ass
ever since you heard

659
00:48:45,964 --> 00:48:47,340
his death sentence
might be commuted.

660
00:48:47,466 --> 00:48:48,424
Just give me five minutes.

661
00:48:48,550 --> 00:48:50,051
You know I can't do that.

662
00:48:50,177 --> 00:48:52,178
And besides, the last time
l gave you five minutes,

663
00:48:52,304 --> 00:48:53,638
you almost put him
in the infirmary.

664
00:48:53,764 --> 00:48:56,724
That was my son, Russell.

665
00:48:56,850 --> 00:49:01,771
I know.

666
00:49:01,897 --> 00:49:06,108
But I can't help you, Tom.

667
00:49:08,612 --> 00:49:10,696
Please don't come here anymore.

668
00:49:32,302 --> 00:49:36,013
<i>Opening exit.</i>

669
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:38,057
<i>Have a good night.</i>

670
00:49:38,183 --> 00:49:39,558
Look, you're trying
to make this case

671
00:49:39,685 --> 00:49:41,644
about a guy
who was found innocent,

672
00:49:41,770 --> 00:49:43,729
who's already serving
a life sentence,

673
00:49:43,855 --> 00:49:45,731
and whatever shit
you think you have on him,

674
00:49:45,857 --> 00:49:47,650
he can't be tried
for it again anyway.

675
00:49:47,776 --> 00:49:49,694
All right...

676
00:49:49,820 --> 00:49:51,404
someone owes me a drink.

677
00:49:51,530 --> 00:49:53,322
This took a lot longer
than I thought it would,

678
00:49:53,448 --> 00:49:56,409
but your idea...

679
00:49:56,535 --> 00:49:58,536
was brilliant.

680
00:49:58,662 --> 00:49:59,954
ls that the-

681
00:50:00,080 --> 00:50:01,455
That's the boy?

682
00:50:01,581 --> 00:50:03,416
I think it's pretty close
to what he looked like.

683
00:50:03,542 --> 00:50:07,753
This is unbelievable work,
Lisa.

684
00:50:07,879 --> 00:50:10,881
We got to get this out
to all the channels we know.

685
00:50:11,008 --> 00:50:13,009
l'm on it.

686
00:50:33,989 --> 00:50:34,864
lt's not right.

687
00:50:34,990 --> 00:50:37,074
l mean,
he's a good kid.

688
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:40,911
l'm tired.

689
00:50:41,038 --> 00:50:42,913
I know, me too.

690
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:44,999
What's the matter, Pa?

691
00:50:45,125 --> 00:50:46,208
You sad?

692
00:50:46,334 --> 00:50:48,294
Yeah, John, l'm sad.

693
00:50:48,420 --> 00:50:51,464
Sad like Mama was sad?

694
00:50:51,590 --> 00:50:52,506
No.

695
00:50:52,632 --> 00:50:55,468
No, not like your mama was sad.

696
00:50:55,594 --> 00:50:57,386
Okay.

697
00:50:57,512 --> 00:50:59,805
Hey, Christian, l...

698
00:50:59,931 --> 00:51:02,016
l wish there was something
l could do to help you.

699
00:51:02,142 --> 00:51:03,809
I got to go.

700
00:51:03,935 --> 00:51:04,935
l got to get out of here.

701
00:51:05,062 --> 00:51:06,687
You ready to go, John?

702
00:51:06,813 --> 00:51:09,398
But l'm the co-pilot,
not you.

703
00:51:09,524 --> 00:51:10,608
Hold on.

704
00:51:10,734 --> 00:51:12,026
This might just be
your lucky night.

705
00:51:12,152 --> 00:51:14,361
What are you talking about?

706
00:51:14,488 --> 00:51:16,489
I think it's pretty damn clear
what l'm talking about,

707
00:51:16,615 --> 00:51:17,490
don't you think?

708
00:51:17,616 --> 00:51:18,824
You just let me do the talking,
shy boy.

709
00:51:18,950 --> 00:51:20,284
Hello there.

710
00:51:20,410 --> 00:51:21,619
Hey.

711
00:51:21,745 --> 00:51:22,661
This is your son, right?

712
00:51:22,788 --> 00:51:24,663
Yeah, this is John.

713
00:51:24,790 --> 00:51:25,664
Hello.

714
00:51:25,791 --> 00:51:26,665
Oh, my.

715
00:51:26,792 --> 00:51:29,376
Aren't you a polite little man?

716
00:51:29,503 --> 00:51:31,337
We were never
properly introduced.

717
00:51:31,463 --> 00:51:32,338
l'm Rose Montgomery.

718
00:51:32,464 --> 00:51:33,339
Matthew Wakefield.

719
00:51:33,465 --> 00:51:35,716
They call me Diploma.

720
00:51:35,842 --> 00:51:37,384
l'm glad to have a chance
to see you again.

721
00:51:37,511 --> 00:51:38,719
Did you find a job?

722
00:51:38,845 --> 00:51:40,679
lt's so funny you should
mention that, actually,

723
00:51:40,806 --> 00:51:42,348
we were just discussing
a situation that's arisen.

724
00:51:42,474 --> 00:51:43,808
Papa, l'm ready
to go to bed now.

725
00:51:43,934 --> 00:51:45,101
l'm sorry, am I keeping you?

726
00:51:45,227 --> 00:51:46,393
No, not at all.

727
00:51:46,520 --> 00:51:48,479
Christian and I were just about
to have another drink.

728
00:51:48,605 --> 00:51:49,855
Christian?

729
00:51:49,981 --> 00:51:51,607
Just a nickname we gave
ol' Matty boy here.

730
00:51:51,733 --> 00:51:52,691
Come on, Matty.

731
00:51:52,818 --> 00:51:54,318
Be a gentleman;
buy the nice lady a drink.

732
00:51:54,444 --> 00:51:55,986
Let John sleep in the car.

733
00:51:57,197 --> 00:51:58,948
Paradise cocktail, Mike.

734
00:51:59,074 --> 00:52:01,367
Diploma, I got to get him
to bed.

735
00:52:03,078 --> 00:52:06,872
Could you excuse us
just one second?

736
00:52:06,998 --> 00:52:11,919
Uh, look after the boy,
would you?

737
00:52:15,215 --> 00:52:16,549
What the hell are you doing?

738
00:52:16,675 --> 00:52:18,551
You're looking for someone
to look after your kid,

739
00:52:18,677 --> 00:52:20,177
and she's standing
right in front of you.

740
00:52:20,303 --> 00:52:21,720
Diploma, she's got a husband.

741
00:52:21,847 --> 00:52:23,764
Matty, I know you've seen
the way she's looking at you.

742
00:52:23,890 --> 00:52:25,850
You make that woman smile,
she'll do anything you ask.

743
00:52:29,020 --> 00:52:29,937
I can't.

744
00:52:30,063 --> 00:52:30,938
lt ain't right.

745
00:52:32,065 --> 00:52:33,566
"lt ain't right."

746
00:52:33,692 --> 00:52:35,943
What is right,
you losing yourjob?

747
00:52:36,069 --> 00:52:38,028
Think about the boy.

748
00:52:38,155 --> 00:52:40,865
Come on.

749
00:52:40,991 --> 00:52:43,200
So you two got it
all worked out?

750
00:52:43,326 --> 00:52:44,785
I believe we do.

751
00:52:44,911 --> 00:52:48,831
Christian?

752
00:52:48,957 --> 00:52:50,124
See you tomorrow.

753
00:52:54,838 --> 00:52:55,754
So can I get you a drink?

754
00:52:56,923 --> 00:52:57,965
l already have one.

755
00:53:00,844 --> 00:53:02,845
Are you sure this is okay,
us having a drink together?

756
00:53:02,971 --> 00:53:05,931
l mean, with your husband
and all?

757
00:53:06,057 --> 00:53:08,100
l'm a big girl.

758
00:53:10,312 --> 00:53:11,770
You a big boy?

759
00:53:13,648 --> 00:53:15,900
Papa.

760
00:53:16,943 --> 00:53:19,111
l'm sorry.

761
00:53:19,237 --> 00:53:20,738
l got to get him home.

762
00:53:20,864 --> 00:53:24,033
Good-bye.

763
00:53:24,159 --> 00:53:25,367
lf you change your mind.

764
00:53:31,917 --> 00:53:32,917
Come on, John.

765
00:53:40,842 --> 00:53:42,259
We've got a bit of a drive
in front of us,

766
00:53:42,385 --> 00:53:43,886
so why don't you get in the back
and lay down

767
00:53:44,012 --> 00:53:45,888
and go to sleep, all right?

768
00:53:46,014 --> 00:53:47,848
- Okay.
- Okay.

769
00:53:47,974 --> 00:53:50,267
Go on in there, lie down.

770
00:53:56,441 --> 00:53:58,525
l'm just gonna cover you up,
all right?

771
00:53:58,652 --> 00:54:00,694
When am I gonna see
the nice lady again?

772
00:54:00,820 --> 00:54:01,737
You liked her?

773
00:54:01,863 --> 00:54:03,656
Mm-hmm.

774
00:54:03,782 --> 00:54:04,990
l thought she was pretty.

775
00:54:05,116 --> 00:54:07,826
Yeah?

776
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:11,664
Here, look, you just stay put.

777
00:54:11,790 --> 00:54:13,040
l'll be back in a few minutes,
okay?

778
00:54:13,166 --> 00:54:14,458
Go ahead and go to sleep.

779
00:54:14,584 --> 00:54:17,419
Whatever you do,
you do not leave this car, John.

780
00:54:21,424 --> 00:54:23,634
John?

781
00:54:51,496 --> 00:54:53,205
Come on.

782
00:54:53,331 --> 00:54:55,165
That's all you got?

783
00:55:38,084 --> 00:55:39,376
Papa?

784
00:55:46,426 --> 00:55:48,761
Maybe we could make this...

785
00:55:48,887 --> 00:55:50,637
a regular thing.

786
00:55:50,764 --> 00:55:53,766
Huh?

787
00:55:53,892 --> 00:55:59,271
You could, uh, give me a hand
with my boy some days.

788
00:55:59,397 --> 00:56:00,439
Huh?

789
00:56:05,445 --> 00:56:08,280
What?
What's funny?

790
00:56:08,406 --> 00:56:11,116
Well, you just got it
all figured out, don't you?

791
00:56:16,915 --> 00:56:19,291
Oh, hey, come on, don't be mad.

792
00:56:19,417 --> 00:56:22,211
Come on.

793
00:56:22,337 --> 00:56:24,338
This was a mistake.

794
00:56:24,464 --> 00:56:26,423
l got to get back to my boy.

795
00:56:26,549 --> 00:56:28,592
Come-

796
00:56:45,527 --> 00:56:48,153
Damn it!

797
00:56:52,784 --> 00:56:54,743
John? John?

798
00:56:57,414 --> 00:56:58,497
Have you seen my boy, my son?

799
00:56:58,623 --> 00:57:00,165
No, kids aren't allowed
in here.

800
00:57:00,291 --> 00:57:01,166
What?

801
00:57:01,292 --> 00:57:02,751
My boy was just here.

802
00:57:02,877 --> 00:57:04,461
Look, I don't want
any trouble, all right?

803
00:57:04,587 --> 00:57:05,546
What are you talking about?

804
00:57:05,672 --> 00:57:06,547
Don't lie to me.

805
00:57:06,673 --> 00:57:07,548
Have you seen my son?

806
00:57:07,674 --> 00:57:10,008
Not since you left with him.

807
00:57:10,135 --> 00:57:11,802
John?

808
00:57:13,471 --> 00:57:15,305
John?

809
00:57:16,808 --> 00:57:18,767
Rose! Rose!

810
00:57:21,688 --> 00:57:33,407
John!

811
00:57:44,335 --> 00:57:45,210
John?

812
00:57:45,336 --> 00:57:46,920
John.

813
00:57:47,046 --> 00:57:49,715
What in God's name?

814
00:57:49,841 --> 00:57:50,716
- Have you seen him?
- Who?

815
00:57:50,842 --> 00:57:53,135
- Have you seen my son?
- No.

816
00:58:08,443 --> 00:58:10,986
Hold on.

817
00:58:14,407 --> 00:58:16,450
Christian,
what the hell are you-

818
00:58:16,576 --> 00:58:17,534
- What's wrong?
- lt's John.

819
00:58:17,660 --> 00:58:18,535
What happened?

820
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:21,705
I can't find John.

821
00:58:21,831 --> 00:58:23,832
Let me get some clothes on.
Hold on.

822
00:58:29,881 --> 00:58:30,923
Johnny!

823
00:58:31,049 --> 00:58:33,258
John!

824
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:36,011
l'm sorry to get you
out of bed, Mike.

825
00:58:36,137 --> 00:58:37,930
lt's okay, chief,
l just don't want any trouble.

826
00:58:38,056 --> 00:58:39,681
Oh, don't worry.

827
00:58:39,807 --> 00:58:41,183
He saw my kid.

828
00:58:41,309 --> 00:58:42,267
He served all three of us.

829
00:58:42,393 --> 00:58:43,268
He gave him a root beer!

830
00:58:43,394 --> 00:58:45,229
All right, all right.

831
00:58:45,355 --> 00:58:46,939
Mike, you leveling with me
or not?

832
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:48,565
You know I don't want kids
in that bar.

833
00:58:48,691 --> 00:58:50,859
No, I wouldn't do something
crazy like that, chief.

834
00:58:50,985 --> 00:58:51,944
Now, officer, that's a lie.

835
00:58:52,070 --> 00:58:52,945
The boy was in the bar,

836
00:58:53,071 --> 00:58:54,363
and there was another girl
in there

837
00:58:54,489 --> 00:58:55,614
who could back us up on that.

838
00:58:55,740 --> 00:58:56,907
What girl?

839
00:59:01,996 --> 00:59:03,872
l asked you what girl?

840
00:59:03,998 --> 00:59:07,042
Her name was Rose.

841
00:59:07,168 --> 00:59:08,961
George's Rose?

842
00:59:09,087 --> 00:59:09,962
She came in after we did.

843
00:59:10,088 --> 00:59:11,296
She ordered a paradise cocktail.

844
00:59:11,422 --> 00:59:13,382
You've got to remember that.

845
00:59:13,508 --> 00:59:16,635
ls that true, Mikey?

846
00:59:16,761 --> 00:59:18,470
- No, Rose wasn't in there.
- You son of a bitch.

847
00:59:18,596 --> 00:59:19,555
My boy is missing.

848
00:59:19,681 --> 00:59:21,974
- You're lying through your teeth!
- Hey!

849
00:59:22,100 --> 00:59:24,059
Mikey, go inside.

850
00:59:24,185 --> 00:59:25,644
That's it, you're just gonna
let him go?

851
00:59:25,770 --> 00:59:27,771
Hey, you want to come with me
to the filling station

852
00:59:27,897 --> 00:59:30,482
and ask George if his wife's
been out alone?

853
00:59:30,608 --> 00:59:31,900
'Cause we can do that.

854
00:59:33,611 --> 00:59:34,987
You're a real gentleman,
aren't you?

855
00:59:35,113 --> 00:59:36,780
lt don't matter if my son
was in the bar or not.

856
00:59:36,906 --> 00:59:38,156
He's missing.

857
00:59:38,283 --> 00:59:39,658
l'm just asking to give me
a few more men

858
00:59:39,784 --> 00:59:40,659
to help look for him.

859
00:59:40,785 --> 00:59:42,035
l'm gonna need your names.

860
00:59:42,161 --> 00:59:46,665
I don't want trouble
with the law.

861
00:59:46,791 --> 00:59:49,334
Sorry, Christian.

862
00:59:49,460 --> 00:59:51,169
You come to the station
in the morning.

863
00:59:51,296 --> 00:59:53,839
File a missing person's report.

864
00:59:53,965 --> 00:59:55,299
We'll talk then.

865
00:59:56,801 --> 00:59:57,759
That's it?

866
00:59:57,885 --> 00:59:59,428
That's it?

867
00:59:59,554 --> 01:00:01,054
My son is missing now.

868
01:00:03,474 --> 01:00:05,100
All right, come on, Christian,

869
01:00:05,226 --> 01:00:07,144
he's not gonna
do anything tonight.

870
01:00:07,270 --> 01:00:08,520
Come on.

871
01:00:08,646 --> 01:00:10,814
We'll keep looking.
We'll find him.

872
01:00:26,414 --> 01:00:27,873
Christian, what are we doing
this far out?

873
01:00:27,999 --> 01:00:30,334
Everybody has to come by here.

874
01:00:45,308 --> 01:00:48,060
We're closed.

875
01:00:53,900 --> 01:00:55,108
Thought we had an understanding.

876
01:00:55,234 --> 01:00:58,612
My boy,
my son's gone missing.

877
01:00:58,738 --> 01:01:00,697
The retard?

878
01:01:00,823 --> 01:01:02,240
ls everything all right?

879
01:01:02,367 --> 01:01:05,619
Yeah, seems, uh,
the retard boy went missing.

880
01:01:05,745 --> 01:01:06,787
Call him that again,

881
01:01:06,913 --> 01:01:08,789
so help me God,
l'll rip your head off.

882
01:01:08,915 --> 01:01:09,831
Let him go.

883
01:01:09,957 --> 01:01:11,583
Christian, it's not worth it.

884
01:01:11,709 --> 01:01:14,920
He don't understand.

885
01:01:15,046 --> 01:01:16,338
What can we do?

886
01:01:16,464 --> 01:01:17,631
You see him, you call me.

887
01:01:17,757 --> 01:01:20,384
Someone comes by here with him,
you get their plates,

888
01:01:20,510 --> 01:01:21,385
you call me.

889
01:01:21,511 --> 01:01:22,386
l'm at Birdie Wheeler's.

890
01:01:22,512 --> 01:01:24,596
All right, consider it done.

891
01:01:27,016 --> 01:01:28,600
All right, where to next?

892
01:01:28,726 --> 01:01:29,851
l'm gonna take you home.

893
01:03:35,853 --> 01:03:37,395
Christian.

894
01:03:37,522 --> 01:03:39,147
Did you find him?

895
01:03:39,273 --> 01:03:40,148
No.

896
01:03:40,274 --> 01:03:41,149
Any sign of him here?

897
01:03:41,275 --> 01:03:43,026
No.

898
01:03:43,152 --> 01:03:44,027
I looked everywhere.

899
01:03:44,153 --> 01:03:45,737
l called all morning for him.

900
01:03:45,863 --> 01:03:47,197
Nothing's happening,
but nothing.

901
01:03:47,323 --> 01:03:50,617
Did you go to the police
this morning?

902
01:03:50,743 --> 01:03:53,203
Yeah, he listened to
everything I had to say, but...

903
01:03:53,329 --> 01:03:56,164
l could see in his eyes
he ain't gonna do nothing.

904
01:03:56,290 --> 01:03:57,457
l got to keep searching.

905
01:03:57,583 --> 01:04:00,460
l want to thank you
for being a good friend to us.

906
01:04:09,887 --> 01:04:10,971
How's he doing?

907
01:04:15,309 --> 01:04:18,103
I hate to see a good man
suffer like that.

908
01:04:18,229 --> 01:04:20,188
You think he'll find his kid?

909
01:04:27,154 --> 01:04:28,655
We have to pour the cement.

910
01:04:28,781 --> 01:04:31,491
All right.

911
01:05:10,156 --> 01:05:12,240
<i>Four days ago
in this very hole,</i>

912
01:05:12,366 --> 01:05:16,161
<i>a gruesome discovery has
shocked our quiet community.</i>

913
01:05:16,287 --> 01:05:18,580
<i>ln a wooden box,
the body of a child,</i>

914
01:05:18,706 --> 01:05:21,458
<i>a boy between the ages of eight
and ten was unearthed</i>

915
01:05:21,584 --> 01:05:24,961
<i>at the Byrnes construction site
on North Dixon.</i>

916
01:05:25,087 --> 01:05:27,964
<i>And once again,
this town finds itself asking,</i>

917
01:05:28,090 --> 01:05:29,132
<i>"Why?"</i>

918
01:05:29,258 --> 01:05:30,550
<i>For Detective Tom Adkins,</i>

919
01:05:30,676 --> 01:05:32,594
<i>whose boy went missing
eight years ago</i>

920
01:05:32,720 --> 01:05:34,346
<i>along with three other
children,</i>

921
01:05:34,472 --> 01:05:37,015
<i>the find
was particularly troubling.</i>

922
01:05:37,141 --> 01:05:40,810
<i>WXlW Channel 2 News nowjoins
Detective Tom Adkins</i>

923
01:05:40,937 --> 01:05:44,689
<i>of the Barnstable police
department live at the scene.</i>

924
01:05:44,815 --> 01:05:46,858
Through my office at the
Barnstable police department,

925
01:05:46,984 --> 01:05:51,237
any questions should be
directed there.

926
01:05:51,364 --> 01:05:52,530
Needless to say,

927
01:05:52,657 --> 01:05:55,533
we have very little information
as to the identity-

928
01:05:55,660 --> 01:05:57,702
Andrews, what's up?

929
01:05:57,828 --> 01:05:59,162
No, I can't deal with that
right now.

930
01:05:59,288 --> 01:06:00,705
l'm here over
at the construction site

931
01:06:00,831 --> 01:06:03,917
for the boy in the box
press conference.

932
01:06:04,043 --> 01:06:05,377
Yeah, well, what do you
want me to do?

933
01:06:05,503 --> 01:06:08,797
Get Susie on it.

934
01:06:15,846 --> 01:06:18,098
Help you with something, sir?

935
01:06:18,224 --> 01:06:20,850
No, I was just wondering
what's going on.

936
01:06:20,977 --> 01:06:22,519
They talking about
that boy they found?

937
01:06:22,645 --> 01:06:23,687
Yes, sir.

938
01:06:23,813 --> 01:06:26,731
Yeah, I read it
in the newspaper.

939
01:06:26,857 --> 01:06:29,150
- Sorry to trouble you.
- Oh, it's no trouble.

940
01:06:29,276 --> 01:06:30,360
Heck of a ride you got here,
huh?

941
01:06:30,486 --> 01:06:34,614
Oh, thank you.

942
01:06:45,418 --> 01:06:48,253
Thanks, Chris.

943
01:06:48,379 --> 01:06:50,255
Well, if that doesn't get 'em,
nothing will.

944
01:06:50,381 --> 01:06:52,048
Hey, Sarge,
l don't know if it's anything,

945
01:06:52,174 --> 01:06:53,967
but I got a plate number
on an old Chevelle.

946
01:06:54,093 --> 01:06:55,510
Seen it around here
a couple times.

947
01:06:55,636 --> 01:06:57,762
Looked like he wanted to
snoop around but didn't dare.

948
01:06:57,888 --> 01:06:58,763
All right, well...

949
01:06:58,889 --> 01:06:59,931
stay on top of it.

950
01:07:03,602 --> 01:07:04,978
Hey, Sarge?

951
01:07:05,104 --> 01:07:06,104
About time you boys got back.

952
01:07:06,230 --> 01:07:07,355
What do you got?

953
01:07:07,481 --> 01:07:09,441
Phones started ringing
off the hook 20 minutes ago.

954
01:07:09,567 --> 01:07:12,610
Maybe we're onto something.

955
01:07:12,737 --> 01:07:14,404
You get started on these.

956
01:07:14,530 --> 01:07:15,780
Call DMV about that
old Chevelle.

957
01:07:15,906 --> 01:07:18,033
Yep, l'm on it.

958
01:07:24,331 --> 01:07:25,623
Don't forget about
Mrs. Adams.

959
01:07:53,110 --> 01:07:55,862
<i>Fiola and Kramer
Toys and Novelties.</i>

960
01:08:02,036 --> 01:08:03,870
<i>My best guess
is that it's some sort of toy.</i>

961
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:07,040
<i>Hello?</i>

962
01:08:07,166 --> 01:08:10,376
Mrs. Adams,
this is Detective Adkins.

963
01:08:40,783 --> 01:08:42,408
Hello?

964
01:08:42,535 --> 01:08:44,410
May I help you?

965
01:08:44,537 --> 01:08:46,037
Mrs. Adams?

966
01:08:46,163 --> 01:08:47,997
l'm Detective Tom Adkins.

967
01:08:48,124 --> 01:08:49,707
This is Pete Dunn.

968
01:08:49,834 --> 01:08:52,544
We're here about
the boy we found.

969
01:08:52,670 --> 01:08:54,129
You called us?

970
01:08:54,255 --> 01:08:57,048
I didn't expect you so soon.

971
01:08:57,174 --> 01:08:59,926
Please call me Edvena.

972
01:09:00,052 --> 01:09:04,556
So when Uncle Matthew came back
to get the other two boys,

973
01:09:04,682 --> 01:09:07,517
there was a lot of whispering
between Ma and Pa.

974
01:09:07,643 --> 01:09:09,561
Excuse me, other boys?

975
01:09:09,687 --> 01:09:10,937
John wasn't an only child?

976
01:09:11,063 --> 01:09:13,690
Oh, heavens, no.

977
01:09:13,816 --> 01:09:16,442
Mark, he was the eldest.

978
01:09:16,569 --> 01:09:17,944
Flying was his passion.

979
01:09:18,070 --> 01:09:19,737
A hero in Vietnam.

980
01:09:19,864 --> 01:09:21,739
He died young, though.

981
01:09:21,866 --> 01:09:24,909
Just a few years
after his father.

982
01:09:25,035 --> 01:09:26,411
And the-
the other son?

983
01:09:26,537 --> 01:09:28,955
Luke.

984
01:09:29,081 --> 01:09:30,665
Luke just sort of...

985
01:09:30,791 --> 01:09:32,542
drifted away from us.

986
01:09:32,668 --> 01:09:34,627
People do that, you know.

987
01:09:34,753 --> 01:09:37,172
You, um...
you mentioned a home?

988
01:09:37,298 --> 01:09:39,048
Uncle Matthew told everyone

989
01:09:39,175 --> 01:09:41,426
that John was being
taken care of

990
01:09:41,552 --> 01:09:45,471
in a place
for backward children.

991
01:09:45,598 --> 01:09:47,182
Backward?

992
01:09:47,308 --> 01:09:49,851
I just saw him that once,

993
01:09:49,977 --> 01:09:51,978
but you could never forget him.

994
01:09:52,104 --> 01:09:55,440
He was the sweetest boy.

995
01:09:55,566 --> 01:09:57,942
l remember he kept showing me

996
01:09:58,068 --> 01:10:02,238
this half-dollar
that someone gave him.

997
01:10:03,866 --> 01:10:06,951
Such sadness.

998
01:10:10,331 --> 01:10:12,582
Do you have children, Detective?

999
01:10:34,480 --> 01:10:35,480
That the one?

1000
01:10:35,606 --> 01:10:36,856
That's the one.

1001
01:10:38,776 --> 01:10:40,318
No mistaking that, huh?

1002
01:10:48,077 --> 01:10:51,079
Can I help you?

1003
01:10:51,205 --> 01:10:52,664
Luke Wakefield?

1004
01:10:52,790 --> 01:10:53,998
Yes, sir.

1005
01:10:54,124 --> 01:10:56,709
l'm Detective Tom Adkins
from over in Barnstable.

1006
01:10:56,835 --> 01:11:00,964
l'd like to talk to you
about your brother John.

1007
01:11:01,090 --> 01:11:03,633
ls there someplace maybe
we can go sit down?

1008
01:11:03,759 --> 01:11:07,262
Sure, yeah, we can
go right in the back here.

1009
01:11:09,640 --> 01:11:12,934
And all this time
you believed John was in a home?

1010
01:11:13,060 --> 01:11:14,602
Well, no,
when I got old enough,

1011
01:11:14,728 --> 01:11:17,146
l asked my dad about John.

1012
01:11:17,273 --> 01:11:20,400
l had this idea
that I wanted to go visit him.

1013
01:11:20,526 --> 01:11:21,651
And that's when my dad
said to me

1014
01:11:21,777 --> 01:11:25,154
that John had gotten sick
and died.

1015
01:11:25,281 --> 01:11:26,906
Look, Detective,
l got to be honest with you,

1016
01:11:27,032 --> 01:11:28,908
none of this
makes any sense whatsoever.

1017
01:11:29,034 --> 01:11:30,618
He was a good man.

1018
01:11:30,744 --> 01:11:33,621
Well, as you can see,
there are some...

1019
01:11:33,747 --> 01:11:37,250
discrepancies
we'd like to clear up.

1020
01:11:37,376 --> 01:11:38,459
Now, is there anybody else

1021
01:11:38,585 --> 01:11:42,380
that we can talk to
about your father?

1022
01:11:45,509 --> 01:11:48,177
Come in, Luke.

1023
01:11:48,304 --> 01:11:50,555
These gentlemen would like to
talk to you about Dad.

1024
01:11:50,681 --> 01:11:52,557
- That'd be okay?
- Well, yes.

1025
01:11:52,683 --> 01:11:55,310
Mrs. Wakefield,
l'm Detective Tom Adkins

1026
01:11:55,436 --> 01:11:59,105
from the Barnstable
police department.

1027
01:11:59,231 --> 01:12:03,776
l'm sorry to say
l have some terribly sad news.

1028
01:12:03,902 --> 01:12:06,279
We recently found the body
of a young boy

1029
01:12:06,405 --> 01:12:09,240
we believe to be that of-

1030
01:12:09,366 --> 01:12:11,284
of John Wakefield.

1031
01:12:11,410 --> 01:12:14,579
Hmm.

1032
01:12:14,705 --> 01:12:18,249
After all this time.

1033
01:12:18,375 --> 01:12:20,835
Matthew would have been
so relieved.

1034
01:12:20,961 --> 01:12:24,464
His boy John.

1035
01:12:25,758 --> 01:12:27,633
That's how we met.

1036
01:12:31,388 --> 01:12:32,597
- Hey, Sally Ann.
- Hmm?

1037
01:12:32,723 --> 01:12:33,723
lt don't have to be perfect.

1038
01:12:33,849 --> 01:12:35,016
This ain't the Waldorf-Astoria.

1039
01:12:35,142 --> 01:12:36,809
You got that right, Chollie.

1040
01:12:36,935 --> 01:12:38,936
See you tomorrow.

1041
01:12:44,902 --> 01:12:49,030
We're closed.

1042
01:12:54,411 --> 01:12:55,495
Hi.

1043
01:12:55,621 --> 01:12:58,998
Could you spare a coffee?

1044
01:12:59,124 --> 01:13:02,460
Sure.

1045
01:13:02,586 --> 01:13:04,003
Where are your boys?

1046
01:13:22,773 --> 01:13:26,776
lt was very sad, really.

1047
01:13:26,902 --> 01:13:28,069
Yes, ma'am.

1048
01:13:36,578 --> 01:13:37,453
